SIMPLE: unembarrassed
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unembarrassed
<hw>Un`em*bar"rassed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not
embarrassed.</def> <specif>Specifically:</specif> --⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(a)</sd> <def>Not perplexed in mind; not confused; as, the
speaker appeared <xex>unembarrassed</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(b)</sd> <def>Free from pecuniary difficulties or encumbrances;
<as>as, he and his property are <ex>unembarrassed</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(c)</sd> <def>Free from perplexing connection; as, the question
comes into court <xex>unembarrassed</xex> with irrelevant
matter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unembarrassment</ent>⟦br⟧
